        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(tui): respect queue mode in sendMessage busy guard",
        "body": "Fixes #89059\nFixes #90012\n\n## Summary\n\nThe TUI `sendMessage()` hardcodes a busy check that blocks new messages when the agent is running, completely ignoring the `/queue` mode setting configured on the Gateway. This makes `followup`, `collect`, and `interrupt` modes unusable from the TUI because messages are rejected at the client layer before reaching the Gateway's queue system.\n\n## Changes\n\n**Gateway session row** (`session-utils.types.ts`, `session-utils.ts`): Add `queueMode` to `GatewaySessionRow` and populate it from the session entry so the TUI can read the session's queue mode.\n\n**TUI types** (`tui-types.ts`, `tui-backend.ts`): Add `queueMode` to `SessionInfo` and the `TuiSessionList` sessions Pick so the TUI can read the session's queue mode.\n\n**TUI session propagation** (`tui-session-actions.ts`): Propagate `queueMode` from the session entry to `state.sessionInfo` during `applySessionInfo`.\n\n**TUI busy guard** (`tui-command-handlers.ts`): Gate the `activeChatRunId` and `pendingChatRunId` checks on `effectiveQueueMode === \"steer\"`. When the mode is `followup`, `collect`, or `interrupt`, the message is forwarded to the Gateway for queue handling. The `pendingOptimisticUserMessage` guard remains unconditional to prevent rapid double-sends while the previous RPC is in flight.\n\n**Catch block fix (P1):** When a queued followup send fails, preserve the prior `activeChatRunId` instead of clearing it. A failed enqueue should not forget the still-running active turn.\n\n**Typed-submit gate** (`tui.ts`): Update `canSubmitTuiChatMessage` to accept and honor `queueMode`. In steer mode (default), it blocks gateway sends during active runs and when a pending chat run exists. In non-steer modes, only `pendingOptimisticUserMessage` blocks.\n\n**Tests**: 9 new tests: 5 for `canSubmitTuiChatMessage` (followup/collect/interrupt allow, steer blocks, pendingOptimistic still blocks in followup), and 4 for the command-handler busy guard (followup allows, pendingOptimistic blocks in followup, queued send failure preserves active run, non-queued failure clears active run).\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: TUI sendMessage blocks messages with \"agent is busy\" when the agent is running, regardless of the /queue mode setting. followup, collect, and interrupt modes never reach the Gateway. Additionally, the catch block unconditionally cleared activeChatRunId on failure, forgetting the still-running active turn when a queued send failed.\nReal environment tested: macOS 15.5, Node v22.19, OpenClaw built from patched source at commit a1addc94c0.\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n\nStep 1. Type check, lint, and run tests:\n\n```console\n$ pnpm tsgo:core\n$ node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs src/tui/tui-command-handlers.ts src/tui/tui.ts src/tui/tui-types.ts src/tui/tui-backend.ts src/tui/tui-session-actions.ts src/gateway/session-utils.ts src/gateway/session-utils.types.ts src/tui/tui-command-handlers.test.ts src/tui/tui.test.ts\nFound 0 warnings and 0 errors.\nFinished in 2.9s on 9 files with 242 rules using 1 threads.\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/tui/tui.test.ts src/tui/tui-command-handlers.test.ts\n ✓ |tui| src/tui/tui-command-handlers.test.ts (73 tests) 25ms\n ✓ |tui| src/tui/tui.test.ts (68 tests) 18ms\n Test Files  2 passed (2)\n      Tests  141 passed (141)\n```\n\nStep 2. Build and verify fix in compiled production code:\n\n```console\n$ pnpm build\n[build-all] phase timings: total 77.2s\n$ grep -n 'effectiveQueueMode\\|allowQueuedSend\\|queueMode' dist/tui-DR23uKra.js\n2470:const allowQueuedSend = (state.sessionInfo.queueMode ?? \"steer\") !== \"steer\";\n2471:if (!isBtw && (state.pendingOptimisticUserMessage || !allowQueuedSend && (state.pendingChatRunId || opts.local !== true && state.activeChatRunId))) {\n3589:if (entry?.queueMode !== void 0) next.queueMode = entry.queueMode;\n4218:if ((params.queueMode ?? \"steer\") !== \"steer\") return true;\n```\n\nStep 3. Start gateway to confirm module loads cleanly:\n\n```console\n$ timeout 10 node openclaw.mjs gateway\n[gateway] loading configuration...\n[gateway] starting...\n[gateway] http server listening (9 plugins; 1.9s)\n[gateway] ready\n[gateway] signal SIGTERM received\n[shutdown] completed cleanly in 52ms\n```\n\nEvidence after fix: All 4 queue-mode-aware code paths are present in the compiled TUI bundle. The gateway starts and shuts down cleanly with the patched code. All 141 tests pass (including 9 new queue-mode tests), zero lint errors.\nObserved result after fix: The production `canSubmitTuiChatMessage` gate correctly allows typed messages through in non-steer queue modes (followup, collect, interrupt) while still blocking in steer mode. The catch block preserves `activeChatRunId` when a queued send fails. The compiled dist confirms the fix shipped.\nWhat was not tested: Live TUI interaction with a running agent using `/queue mode=followup` then sending a message mid-run (requires an active provider with credentials and a long-running turn). The end-to-end flow relies on the Gateway's existing queue system which is already tested.\n",
